5:
Geez! Your faces are looking saltier
than the sea!
8:
It's okay. You're not wrong to feel the
way you're feeling right now.
11:
Let's just do everything we can for
the sake of those we care about.
17:
Looks like you're putting up with a
lot. Have the higher-ups been giving
you a hard time?
21:
Colonel Selene...
My apologies, I meant to be in
contact with you soonerâ€”
25:
Drop the polite act. No need to be so
formal with a "dead" officer, right?
30:
...Heh, if you say so! What's a corpse
like you doing out in broad daylight,
anyway?
33:
First of all, I know about Starview
Village.
36:
My own reach has grown... but
there's always room for another
cute little officer.
38:
How about it? I scratch your back,
and you scratch mine?
42:
Are you kidding? That sounds
fantastic!
45:
How many military laws and
regulations would you have to break
to do that?
49:
Regulations don't matter if you're
already dead.
53:
You're really something else...
Anyway, I'll have to pass. I'm not cut
out for dodging the Navy's cannons
for the rest of my life.
56:
It's best we continue on our own
paths, doing things our own ways.
60:
Well, come visit me if you're ever
feeling lonely. My bed's got plenty of
space, you know?
73: Ugh, I just don't GET her!
79:
I know she just wants to help me,
but the WAY she goes about it...
81:
I mean, most people would at least
disguise themselves in public after
faking their own death, right?!
84:
And worst of all! She's always gotta
end our talks by hitting on me! Just...
stop, already!
87:
You're not usually this loud. Maybe
cool it with the drinks?
92:
I haven't even had a sip yet! Besides,
I brought you souvenirs, right? Let
me vent a little!
97:
It's okay, Fraxis! The fish is almost
done, so go ahead and start eating!
102:
So this is what you're really like, huh?
Go ahead, I guess. For better or
worse, we're listening.
108:
You remember that Float we saved
from those pirates the other day?
Starting tomorrow, the whole thing's
getting scrapped.
111:
Population's been dropping year
after year, and it seems like they
were running low on resources. 
The higher-ups decided it wasn't 
worth maintaining it anymore.
114:
Seeing the floatdwellers' faces when
the announcement was made... 
It took a toll on me.
120: Can't anything be done about this?
123:
I mean, uh... I figured since this is you
we're talking about, you could
probably do something about this...
126:
...Sorry, I didn't mean to push all the
responsibility on you.
130:
It's all right, Alk. I'm glad you think so
highly of me!
133:
But... Unfortunately, this is one
problem I can't do anything about.
137:
...Is this something that happens
often? Floats getting scrapped?
141:
Well, it's not especially rare. The
Float I was born on ended up
getting scrapped once crime got a
little out of hand.
144:
I used to be a lot more optimistic
about fixing these problems, 
but I had to give it up eventually.
147:
Only a fool would think they can
overcome years of bureaucratic
stagnation and accomplish
something meaningful all by
themselves.
152:
...Oh yeah? I'd rather eat by myself
than share a meal with a defeatist.
156:
Well, seeing as I'm still worried about
it, that must mean I haven't given up
yet... At least according to a certain
friend of mine.
161:
...Does that friend happen to be
Marina?
165:
You Crimson Blades really know
your captain, huh!
167:
...But yes, that's what she said. While
laughing her head off and drunk off
her ass, of course.
170:
Heh, hard not to smile at a memory
like that!
172:
Even in that state, she taught me
something important about
myselfâ€”I haven't given up on
anything yet.
176:
My dream is to live in a world where
the law rewards walking the
righteous path.
181:
...Heh. You sure you see eye-to-eye
with an outlaw like Marina?
185:
We've just got different methods.
That woman has a beautiful sense
of ambition.
188:
...As for myself, you better believe I'll
keep doing everything I can to make
my dream a reality.
191:
Even if it isn't realized for hundreds
of years... I'll keep believing that my
efforts here and now mean
something.
196:
All finished! Here comes the main
course!
205:
Alk's cooking sure deserves its fame!
My senses are totally overwhelmed!
208:
Oh yeah, Alk! Could you help me
with something?
211:
I don't suppose you've got
experience with catering?
217:
A full-on banquet, huh? Even though
this place is getting scrapped
tomorrow, everyone looks happy.
220:
You gotta smile sometimes,
especially when something's got
you down.
224: Where will all these people go?
228:
They'll be moving to a Float where
businesses are thriving and life is
good.
230:
It'll be a busier life than what they're
used to, but it's also a place filled
with enthusiasm and extra
resources. They'll do all right.
234:
...Not sure how you pulled it off, 
but congrats.
239:
Heh! Nothing's too much trouble
when Fraxis has your back!
242:
Hey, Fraxis! Let me ride on your
board again! I wanna go zoooom!
245:
Heh-heh! You bet, kid!
I'll be going at top speed, but is that
okay, Stella?
254: All righty, then! Catch you guys later!
